31#ifdef V8_OS_WIN
32
33// Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34// BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35// the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36// static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37// BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38#ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
39# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
40#elif USING_V8_SHARED
41# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
42#else
43# define V8_EXPORT
44#endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
45
46#else // V8_OS_WIN
47
48// Setup for Linux shared library export.
49#if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY
50# ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
51# define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
52# else
53# define V8_EXPORT
54# endif
55#else
56# define V8_EXPORT
57#endif
58
59#endif // V8_OS_WIN

165#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
166 while (false) { \
167 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
168 }
169
201template <class T>
202class Local {
203 public:
204 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
205 template <class S>
206 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
207 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
213 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
214 }
215
219 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
220
224 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
225
226 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
227
228 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
229
236 template <class S>
237 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
238 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
239 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
240 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
241 if (b == 0) return false;
242 return *a == *b;
243 }
244
245 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
246 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
247 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
248 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
249 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
250 if (b == 0) return false;
251 return *a == *b;
252 }
253
260 template <class S>
261 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
262 return !operator==(that);
263 }
264
265 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
266 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
267 return !operator==(that);
268 }
269
275 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
276#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
277 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
278 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
279 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
280#endif
281 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
282 }
283
289 template <class S>
290 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
291 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
292 }
293
299 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
300 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
301 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
302
303 private:
304 friend class Utils;
305 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
306 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
307 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
308 template<class F> friend class Local;
309 template <class F>
310 friend class MaybeLocal;
311 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
312 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
313 friend class String;
314 friend class Object;
315 friend class Context;
316 friend class Private;
317 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
318 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
319 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
320 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
321 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
322 friend class HandleScope;
323 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
324 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
325 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
326 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
327 template <class F>
328 friend class ReturnValue;
329
330 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
331 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
332 T* val_;
333};

353template <class T>
354class MaybeLocal {
355 public:
356 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
357 template <class S>
358 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
359 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
360 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
361 }
362
363 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
364
369 template <class S>
370 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
371 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
372 return !IsEmpty();
373 }
374
379 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
380
385 template <class S>
386 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
387 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
388 }
389
390 private:
391 T* val_;
392};

398template <class T> class Eternal {
399 public:
400 V8_INLINE Eternal() : val_(nullptr) {}
401 template <class S>
402 V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : val_(nullptr) {
403 Set(isolate, handle);
404 }
405 // Can only be safely called if already set.
406 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const;
407 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
408 template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
409
410 private:
411 T* val_;
412};

415static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
416static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
417
418template <typename T>
419class WeakCallbackInfo {
420 public:
421 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
422
423 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
424 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
425 Callback* callback)
426 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
427 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
428 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
429 }
430 }
431
432 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
433 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
434 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
435
436 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
437 void* GetInternalField1() const) {
438 return embedder_fields_[0];
439 }
440 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
441 void* GetInternalField2() const) {
442 return embedder_fields_[1];
443 }
444
445 V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
446 bool IsFirstPass() const) {
447 return callback_ != nullptr;
448 }
449
450 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
451 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
452 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
453 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
454 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
455 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
456 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
457
458 private:
459 Isolate* isolate_;
460 T* parameter_;
461 Callback* callback_;
462 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
463};
464
465
466// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
467// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
468// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
469// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
470// possible to request a second pass callback.
471enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
472
486template <class T> class PersistentBase {
487 public:
492 V8_INLINE void Reset();
497 template <class S>
498 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
499
504 template <class S>
505 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
506
507 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == NULL; }
508 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
509
510 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
511 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
512 }
513
514 template <class S>
515 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
516 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
517 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
518 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
519 if (b == NULL) return false;
520 return *a == *b;
521 }
522
523 template <class S>
524 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
525 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
526 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
527 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
528 if (b == NULL) return false;
529 return *a == *b;
530 }
531
532 template <class S>
533 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
534 return !operator==(that);
535 }
536
537 template <class S>
538 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
539 return !operator==(that);
540 }
541
549 template <typename P>
550 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
551 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
552 WeakCallbackType type);
553
561 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();
562
563 template<typename P>
564 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
565
566 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
567 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
568
574 V8_INLINE void RegisterExternalReference(Isolate* isolate) const;
575
582 V8_INLINE void MarkIndependent();
583
589 V8_INLINE void MarkActive();
590
591 V8_INLINE bool IsIndependent() const;
592
594 V8_INLINE bool IsNearDeath() const;
595
597 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
598
603 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
604
609 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
610
611 PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
612 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
613
614 private:
615 friend class Isolate;
616 friend class Utils;
617 template<class F> friend class Local;
618 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
619 template <class F>
620 friend class Global;
621 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
622 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
623 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
624 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
625 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
626 friend class Object;
627
628 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
629 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
630
631 T* val_;
632};

641template<class T>
642class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
643 public:
644 typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
645 static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
646 template<class S, class M>
647 V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
648 NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
649 Uncompilable<Object>();
650 }
651 // TODO(dcarney): come up with a good compile error here.
652 template<class O> V8_INLINE static void Uncompilable() {
653 TYPE_CHECK(O, Primitive);
654 }
655};

662template<class T>
663struct CopyablePersistentTraits {
664 typedef Persistent<T, CopyablePersistentTraits<T> > CopyablePersistent;
665 static const bool kResetInDestructor = true;
666 template<class S, class M>
667 static V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
668 CopyablePersistent* dest) {
669 // do nothing, just allow copy
670 }
671};

682template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
683 public:
687 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
693 template <class S>
694 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
695 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
696 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
697 }
703 template <class S, class M2>
704 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
705 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
706 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
707 }
714 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
715 Copy(that);
716 }
717 template <class S, class M2>
718 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
719 Copy(that);
720 }
721 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
722 Copy(that);
723 return *this;
724 }
725 template <class S, class M2>
726 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
727 Copy(that);
728 return *this;
729 }
735 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
736 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
737 }
738
739 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
740 template <class S>
741 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
742#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
743 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
744 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
745 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
746#endif
747 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
748 }
749
750 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
751 template <class S>
752 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
753 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
754 }
755
756 private:
757 friend class Isolate;
758 friend class Utils;
759 template<class F> friend class Local;
760 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
761 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
762
763 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
764 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
765 template<class S, class M2>
766 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
767};

775template <class T>
776class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
777 public:
781 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
787 template <class S>
788 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
789 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
790 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
791 }
797 template <class S>
798 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
799 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
800 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
801 }
805 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
806 other.val_ = nullptr;
807 }
808 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
812 template <class S>
813 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
814 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
815 if (this != &rhs) {
816 this->Reset();
817 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
818 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
819 }
820 return *this;
821 }
825 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
826
827 /*
828 * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
829 */
830 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
831
832 Global(const Global&) = delete;
833 void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
834
835 private:
836 template <class F>
837 friend class ReturnValue;
838 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
839};

861class V8_EXPORT HandleScope {
862 public:
863 explicit HandleScope(Isolate* isolate);
864
865 ~HandleScope();
866
870 static int NumberOfHandles(Isolate* isolate);
871
872 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const {
873 return reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(isolate_);
874 }
875
876 HandleScope(const HandleScope&) = delete;
877 void operator=(const HandleScope&) = delete;
878
879 protected:
880 V8_INLINE HandleScope() {}
881
882 void Initialize(Isolate* isolate);
883
884 static internal::Object** CreateHandle(internal::Isolate* isolate,
885 internal::Object* value);
886
887 private:
888 // Declaring operator new and delete as deleted is not spec compliant.
889 // Therefore declare them private instead to disable dynamic alloc
890 void* operator new(size_t size);
891 void* operator new[](size_t size);
892 void operator delete(void*, size_t);
893 void operator delete[](void*, size_t);
894
895 // Uses heap_object to obtain the current Isolate.
896 static internal::Object** CreateHandle(internal::HeapObject* heap_object,
897 internal::Object* value);
898
899 internal::Isolate* isolate_;
900 internal::Object** prev_next_;
901 internal::Object** prev_limit_;
902
903 // Local::New uses CreateHandle with an Isolate* parameter.
904 template<class F> friend class Local;
905
906 // Object::GetInternalField and Context::GetEmbedderData use CreateHandle with
907 // a HeapObject* in their shortcuts.
908 friend class Object;
909 friend class Context;
910};

1032class ScriptOriginOptions {
1033 public:
1034 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1035 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1036 bool is_module = false)
1037 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1038 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1039 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1040 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1041 : flags_(flags &
1042 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1043
1044 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1045 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1046 }
1047 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1048 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1049 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1050
1051 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1052
1053 private:
1054 enum {
1055 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1056 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1057 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1058 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1059 };
1060 const int flags_;
1061};

1066class ScriptOrigin {
1067 public:
1068 V8_INLINE ScriptOrigin(
1069 Local<Value> resource_name,

1086 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions Options() const { return options_; }
1087
1088 private:

1268class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1269 public:
1277 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1278 enum BufferPolicy {
1279 BufferNotOwned,
1280 BufferOwned
1281 };
1282
1283 CachedData()
1284 : data(NULL),
1285 length(0),
1286 rejected(false),
1287 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1288
1289 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1290 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1291 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1292 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1293 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1294 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1295 ~CachedData();
1296 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1297 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1298 const uint8_t* data;
1299 int length;
1300 bool rejected;
1301 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1302
1303 // Prevent copying.
1304 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1305 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1306 };
1307
1311 class Source {
1312 public:
1313 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1314 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1315 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1316 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1317 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1318 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1319
1320 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1321 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1322 // alive.
1323 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1324
1325 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1326
1327 // Prevent copying.
1328 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1329 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1330
1331 private:
1332 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1333
1334 Local<String> source_string;
1335
1336 // Origin information
1337 Local<Value> resource_name;
1338 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1339 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1340 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1341 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1342 Local<PrimitiveArray> host_defined_options;
1343
1344 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1345 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1346 // set when calling a compile method.
1347 CachedData* cached_data;
1348 };

1780// A StateTag represents a possible state of the VM.
1781enum StateTag {
1782 JS,
1783 GC,
1784 PARSER,
1785 BYTECODE_COMPILER,
1786 COMPILER,
1787 OTHER,
1788 EXTERNAL,
1789 IDLE
1790};
1791
1792// A RegisterState represents the current state of registers used
1793// by the sampling profiler API.
1794struct RegisterState {
1795 RegisterState() : pc(nullptr), sp(nullptr), fp(nullptr) {}
1796 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
1797 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
1798 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
1799};
1800
1801// The output structure filled up by GetStackSample API function.
1802struct SampleInfo {
1803 size_t frames_count; // Number of frames collected.
1804 StateTag vm_state; // Current VM state.
1805 void* external_callback_entry; // External callback address if VM is
1806 // executing an external callback.
1807};

3118 // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3119 //
3120 // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3121 // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3122 // or the object is not extensible.
3123 //
3124 // Returns true on success.

3134 // In general, CreateDataProperty will be faster, however, does not allow
3135 // for specifying attributes.
3136 //
3137 // Returns true on success.

3139 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, Local<Value> value,
3140 PropertyAttribute attributes = None);
3141
3142 // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3143 //
3144 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3145 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3146 //
3147 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3148 //
3149 // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3150 // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3151 //
3152 // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3153 //
3154 // Returns true on success.
3155 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(
3156 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, PropertyDescriptor& descriptor);
3157
3158 // Sets an own property on this object bypassing interceptors and
3159 // overriding accessors or read-only properties.
3160 //
3161 // Note that if the object has an interceptor the property will be set
3162 // locally, but since the interceptor takes precedence the local property
3163 // will only be returned if the interceptor doesn't return a value.
3164 //
3165 // Note also that this only works for named properties.
3166 V8_DEPRECATED("Use CreateDataProperty / DefineOwnProperty",
3167 Maybe<bool> ForceSet(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key,
3168 Local<Value> value,
3169 PropertyAttribute attribs = None));

3650template<typename T>
3651class ReturnValue {
3652 public:
3653 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3654 : value_(that.value_) {
3655 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3656 }
3657 // Local setters
3658 template <typename S>
3659 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3660 void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3661 template <typename S>
3662 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3663 template <typename S>
3664 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3665 // Fast primitive setters
3666 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3667 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3668 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3669 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3670 // Fast JS primitive setters
3671 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3672 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3673 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3674 // Convenience getter for Isolate
3675 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3676
3677 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3678 template <typename S>
3679 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3680
3681 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3682 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3683 // value.
3684 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3685
3686 private:
3687 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3688 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3689 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3690 template <class F, class G, class H>
3691 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3692 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3693 V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3694 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3695 internal::Object** value_;
3696};

4162// TODO(mtrofin): rename WasmCompiledModule to WasmModuleObject, for
4163// consistency with internal APIs.
4164class V8_EXPORT WasmCompiledModule : public Object {
4165 public:
4166 typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> SerializedModule;
4167 // A buffer that is owned by the caller.
4168 typedef std::pair<const uint8_t*, size_t> CallerOwnedBuffer;
4169
4170 // An opaque, native heap object for transferring wasm modules. It
4171 // supports move semantics, and does not support copy semantics.
4172 class TransferrableModule final {
4173 public:
4174 TransferrableModule(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4175 TransferrableModule(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4176
4177 TransferrableModule& operator=(TransferrableModule&& src) = default;
4178 TransferrableModule& operator=(const TransferrableModule& src) = delete;
4179
4180 private:
4181 typedef std::pair<std::unique_ptr<const uint8_t[]>, size_t> OwnedBuffer;
4182 friend class WasmCompiledModule;
4183 TransferrableModule(OwnedBuffer&& code, OwnedBuffer&& bytes)
4184 : compiled_code(std::move(code)), wire_bytes(std::move(bytes)) {}
4185
4186 OwnedBuffer compiled_code = {nullptr, 0};
4187 OwnedBuffer wire_bytes = {nullptr, 0};
4188 };
4189
4190 // Get an in-memory, non-persistable, and context-independent (meaning,
4191 // suitable for transfer to another Isolate and Context) representation
4192 // of this wasm compiled module.
4193 TransferrableModule GetTransferrableModule();
4194
4195 // Efficiently re-create a WasmCompiledModule, without recompiling, from
4196 // a TransferrableModule.
4197 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> FromTransferrableModule(
4198 Isolate* isolate, const TransferrableModule&);
4199
4200 // Get the wasm-encoded bytes that were used to compile this module.
4201 Local<String> GetWasmWireBytes();
4202
4203 // Serialize the compiled module. The serialized data does not include the
4204 // uncompiled bytes.
4205 SerializedModule Serialize();
4206
4207 // If possible, deserialize the module, otherwise compile it from the provided
4208 // uncompiled bytes.
4209 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> DeserializeOrCompile(
4210 Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4211 const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4212 V8_INLINE static WasmCompiledModule* Cast(Value* obj);
4213
4214 private:
4215 // TODO(ahaas): please remove the friend once streamed compilation is
4216 // implemented
4217 friend class WasmModuleObjectBuilder;
4218
4219 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Deserialize(
4220 Isolate* isolate, const CallerOwnedBuffer& serialized_module,
4221 const CallerOwnedBuffer& wire_bytes);
4222 static MaybeLocal<WasmCompiledModule> Compile(Isolate* isolate,
4223 const uint8_t* start,
4224 size_t length);
4225 static CallerOwnedBuffer AsCallerOwned(
4226 const TransferrableModule::OwnedBuffer& buff) {
4227 return {buff.first.get(), buff.second};
4228 }
4229
4230 WasmCompiledModule();
4231 static void CheckCast(Value* obj);
4232};

5682struct NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {

5685 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter = 0,
5686 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter = 0,
5687 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query = 0,
5688 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter = 0,
5689 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator = 0,
5690 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
5691 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
5692 : getter(getter),
5693 setter(setter),
5694 query(query),
5695 deleter(deleter),
5696 enumerator(enumerator),
5697 definer(0),
5698 descriptor(0),
5699 data(data),
5700 flags(flags) {}
5701
5702 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
5703 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter,
5704 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter,
5705 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor,
5706 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter,
5707 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator,
5708 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer,
5709 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
5710 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
5711 : getter(getter),
5712 setter(setter),
5713 query(0),
5714 deleter(deleter),
5715 enumerator(enumerator),
5716 definer(definer),
5717 descriptor(descriptor),
5718 data(data),
5719 flags(flags) {}
5720
5721 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter;
5722 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter;
5723 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query;
5724 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter;
5725 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator;
5726 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer;
5727 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor;
5728 Local<Value> data;
5729 PropertyHandlerFlags flags;
5730};

6054class V8_EXPORT Extension { // NOLINT
6055 public:
6056 // Note that the strings passed into this constructor must live as long
6057 // as the Extension itself.
6058 Extension(const char* name,
6059 const char* source = 0,
6060 int dep_count = 0,
6061 const char** deps = 0,
6062 int source_length = -1);
6063 virtual ~Extension() { }
6064 virtual Local<FunctionTemplate> GetNativeFunctionTemplate(
6065 Isolate* isolate, Local<String> name) {
6066 return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
6067 }
6068
6069 const char* name() const { return name_; }
6070 size_t source_length() const { return source_length_; }
6071 const String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source() const {
6072 return &source_; }
6073 int dependency_count() { return dep_count_; }
6074 const char** dependencies() { return deps_; }
6075 void set_auto_enable(bool value) { auto_enable_ = value; }
6076 bool auto_enable() { return auto_enable_; }
6077
6078 // Disallow copying and assigning.
6079 Extension(const Extension&) = delete;
6080 void operator=(const Extension&) = delete;
6081
6082 private:
6083 const char* name_;
6084 size_t source_length_; // expected to initialize before source_
6085 ExternalOneByteStringResourceImpl source_;
6086 int dep_count_;
6087 const char** deps_;
6088 bool auto_enable_;
6089};

6116class V8_EXPORT ResourceConstraints {
6117 public:
6118 ResourceConstraints();
6119
6129 void ConfigureDefaults(uint64_t physical_memory,
6130 uint64_t virtual_memory_limit);
6131
6132 // Returns the max semi-space size in MB.
6133 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use max_semi_space_size_in_kb()",
6134 int max_semi_space_size()) {
6135 return static_cast<int>(max_semi_space_size_in_kb_ / 1024);
6136 }
6137
6138 // Sets the max semi-space size in MB.
6139 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use set_max_semi_space_size_in_kb(size_t limit_in_kb)",
6140 void set_max_semi_space_size(int limit_in_mb)) {
6141 max_semi_space_size_in_kb_ = limit_in_mb * 1024;
6142 }
6143
6144 // Returns the max semi-space size in KB.
6145 size_t max_semi_space_size_in_kb() const {
6146 return max_semi_space_size_in_kb_;
6147 }
6148
6149 // Sets the max semi-space size in KB.
6150 void set_max_semi_space_size_in_kb(size_t limit_in_kb) {
6151 max_semi_space_size_in_kb_ = limit_in_kb;
6152 }
6153
6154 int max_old_space_size() const { return max_old_space_size_; }
6155 void set_max_old_space_size(int limit_in_mb) {
6156 max_old_space_size_ = limit_in_mb;
6157 }
6158 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("max_executable_size_ is subsumed by max_old_space_size_",
6159 int max_executable_size() const) {
6160 return max_executable_size_;
6161 }
6162 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("max_executable_size_ is subsumed by max_old_space_size_",
6163 void set_max_executable_size(int limit_in_mb)) {
6164 max_executable_size_ = limit_in_mb;
6165 }
6166 uint32_t* stack_limit() const { return stack_limit_; }
6167 // Sets an address beyond which the VM's stack may not grow.
6168 void set_stack_limit(uint32_t* value) { stack_limit_ = value; }
6169 size_t code_range_size() const { return code_range_size_; }
6170 void set_code_range_size(size_t limit_in_mb) {
6171 code_range_size_ = limit_in_mb;
6172 }
6173 size_t max_zone_pool_size() const { return max_zone_pool_size_; }
6174 void set_max_zone_pool_size(const size_t bytes) {
6175 max_zone_pool_size_ = bytes;
6176 }
6177
6178 private:
6179 // max_semi_space_size_ is in KB
6180 size_t max_semi_space_size_in_kb_;
6181
6182 // The remaining limits are in MB
6183 int max_old_space_size_;
6184 int max_executable_size_;
6185 uint32_t* stack_limit_;
6186 size_t code_range_size_;
6187 size_t max_zone_pool_size_;
6188};

6584struct JitCodeEvent {
6585 enum EventType {
6586 CODE_ADDED,
6587 CODE_MOVED,
6588 CODE_REMOVED,
6589 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6590 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6591 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6592 };
6593 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6594 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6595 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6596 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6597 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6598 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6599
6600 // Type of event.
6601 EventType type;
6602 // Start of the instructions.
6603 void* code_start;
6604 // Size of the instructions.
6605 size_t code_len;
6606 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6607 Local<UnboundScript> script;
6608 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6609 // code line information which is returned from the
6610 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6611 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6612 void* user_data;
6613
6614 struct name_t {
6615 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6616 // zero-terminated.
6617 const char* str;
6618 // Number of chars in str.
6619 size_t len;
6620 };
6621
6622 struct line_info_t {
6623 // PC offset
6624 size_t offset;
6625 // Code position
6626 size_t pos;
6627 // The position type.
6628 PositionType position_type;
6629 };
6630
6631 union {
6632 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6633 struct name_t name;
6634
6635 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6636 struct line_info_t line_info;
6637
6638 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6639 void* new_code_start;
6640 };
6641};
6642
6648enum RAILMode {
6649 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6650 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6651 // Throughput may be throttled.
6652 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6653 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6654 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6655 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6656 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6657 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6658 // in this mode.
6659 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6660 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6661 // turn off latency optimizations.
6662 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6663};
6664
6668enum JitCodeEventOptions {
6669 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
6670 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
6671 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
6672};

8327template <class T>
8328class Maybe {
8329 public:
8330 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8331 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8332
8336 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8337
8342 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8343 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8344 return IsJust();
8345 }
8346
8351 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8352 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8353 return value_;
8354 }
8355
8360 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8361 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8362 }
8363
8364 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8365 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8366 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8367 }
8368
8369 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8370 return !operator==(other);
8371 }
8372
8373 private:
8374 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8375 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8376
8377 bool has_value_;
8378 T value_;
8379
8380 template <class U>
8381 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8382 template <class U>
8383 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8384};
8385
8386
8387template <class T>
8388inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8389 return Maybe<T>();
8390}
8391
8392
8393template <class T>
8394inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8395 return Maybe<T>(t);
8396}

8959
8960namespace internal {
8961
8962const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8963const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8964const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8965
8966// Tag information for HeapObject.
8967const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8968const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8969const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8970
8971// Tag information for Smi.
8972const int kSmiTag = 0;
8973const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8974const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8975
8976template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8977
8978template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8979V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8980 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8981 uintptr_t tagged_value =
8982 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8983 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8984}
8985
8986// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8987template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8988 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8989 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8990 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8991 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8992 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8993 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8994 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8995 }
8996 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8997 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8998 }
8999 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
9000 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
9001 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
9002 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
9003 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
9004 //
9005 // CAUTION: The original code below:
9006 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
9007 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
9008 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
9009 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
9010 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
9011 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
9012 }
9013};
9014
9015// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
9016template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
9017 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
9018 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
9019 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
9020 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
9021 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
9022 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
9023 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
9024 }
9025 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
9026 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
9027 }
9028 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
9029 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
9030 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
9031 }
9032};
9033
9034typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
9035const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
9036const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
9037V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
9038V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }
9039
9045class Internals {
9046 public:
9047 // These values match non-compiler-dependent values defined within
9048 // the implementation of v8.
9049 static const int kHeapObjectMapOffset = 0;
9050 static const int kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset =
9051 1 * kApiPointerSize + kApiIntSize;
9052 static const int kStringResourceOffset = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
9053
9054 static const int kOddballKindOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize + sizeof(double);
9055 static const int kForeignAddressOffset = kApiPointerSize;
9056 static const int kJSObjectHeaderSize = 3 * kApiPointerSize;
9057 static const int kFixedArrayHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
9058 static const int kContextHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;
9059 static const int kContextEmbedderDataIndex = 5;
9060 static const int kFullStringRepresentationMask = 0x0f;
9061 static const int kStringEncodingMask = 0x8;
9062 static const int kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag = 0x02;
9063 static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x0a;
9064
9065 static const int kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset = 0 * kApiPointerSize;
9066 static const int kExternalMemoryOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize;
9067 static const int kExternalMemoryLimitOffset =
9068 kExternalMemoryOffset + kApiInt64Size;
9069 static const int kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset =
9070 kExternalMemoryLimitOffset + kApiInt64Size;
9071 static const int kIsolateRootsOffset = kExternalMemoryLimitOffset +
9072 kApiInt64Size + kApiInt64Size +
9073 kApiPointerSize + kApiPointerSize;
9074 static const int kUndefinedValueRootIndex = 4;
9075 static const int kTheHoleValueRootIndex = 5;
9076 static const int kNullValueRootIndex = 6;
9077 static const int kTrueValueRootIndex = 7;
9078 static const int kFalseValueRootIndex = 8;
9079 static const int kEmptyStringRootIndex = 9;
9080
9081 static const int kNodeClassIdOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize;
9082 static const int kNodeFlagsOffset = 1 * kApiPointerSize + 3;
9083 static const int kNodeStateMask = 0x7;
9084 static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;
9085 static const int kNodeStateIsPendingValue = 3;
9086 static const int kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue = 4;
9087 static const int kNodeIsIndependentShift = 3;
9088 static const int kNodeIsActiveShift = 4;
9089
9090 static const int kFirstNonstringType = 0x80;
9091 static const int kOddballType = 0x83;
9092 static const int kForeignType = 0x87;
9093 static const int kJSApiObjectType = 0xbf;
9094 static const int kJSObjectType = 0xc0;
9095
9096 static const int kUndefinedOddballKind = 5;
9097 static const int kNullOddballKind = 3;
9098
9099 static const uint32_t kNumIsolateDataSlots = 4;
9100
9101 V8_EXPORT static void CheckInitializedImpl(v8::Isolate* isolate);
9102 V8_INLINE static void CheckInitialized(v8::Isolate* isolate) {
9103#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9104 CheckInitializedImpl(isolate);
9105#endif
9106 }
9107
9108 V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {
9109 return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
9110 kHeapObjectTag);
9111 }
9112
9113 V8_INLINE static int SmiValue(const internal::Object* value) {
9114 return PlatformSmiTagging::SmiToInt(value);
9115 }
9116
9117 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
9118 return PlatformSmiTagging::IntToSmi(value);
9119 }
9120
9121 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
9122 return PlatformSmiTagging::IsValidSmi(value);
9123 }
9124
9125 V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
9126 typedef internal::Object O;
9127 O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
9128 // Map::InstanceType is defined so that it will always be loaded into
9129 // the LS 8 bits of one 16-bit word, regardless of endianess.
9130 return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset) & 0xff;
9131 }
9132
9133 V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
9134 typedef internal::Object O;
9135 return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
9136 }
9137
9138 V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
9139 int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
9140 return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
9141 }
9142
9143 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
9144 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9145 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
9146 }
9147
9148 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
9149 bool value, int shift) {
9150 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9151 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
9152 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
9153 }
9154
9155 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
9156 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9157 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
9158 }
9159
9160 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
9161 uint8_t value) {
9162 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
9163 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
9164 }
9165
9166 V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
9167 uint32_t slot,
9168 void* data) {
9169 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
9170 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
9171 *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
9172 }
9173
9174 V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
9175 uint32_t slot) {
9176 const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
9177 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
9178 return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
9179 }
9180
9181 V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
9182 int index) {
9183 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
9184 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
9185 }
9186
9187 template <typename T>
9188 V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
9189 const uint8_t* addr =
9190 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
9191 return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
9192 }
9193
9194 template <typename T>
9195 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
9196 typedef internal::Object O;
9197 typedef internal::Internals I;
9198 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
9199 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
9200 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
9201 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
9202 int value_offset =
9203 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9204 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
9205 }
9206};
9207
9208} // namespace internal

9222template <class T>
9223Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
9224 if (that == NULL) return Local<T>();
9225 T* that_ptr = that;
9226 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that_ptr);
9227 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
9228 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
9229}

9237 V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));

9266template <class T>
9267T* PersistentBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
9268 if (that == NULL) return NULL;
9269 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that);
9270 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
9271 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
9272 p));
9273}

9276template <class T, class M>
9277template <class S, class M2>
9278void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
9279 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9280 this->Reset();
9281 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
9282 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
9283 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
9284 M::Copy(that, this);
9285}

9288template <class T>
9289bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
9290 typedef internal::Internals I;
9291 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9292 return I::GetNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_),
9293 I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
9294}
9295
9296
9297template <class T>
9298bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
9299 typedef internal::Internals I;
9300 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9301 uint8_t node_state =
9302 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9303 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
9304 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
9305}
9306
9307
9308template <class T>
9309bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
9310 typedef internal::Internals I;
9311 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9312 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)) ==
9313 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
9314}

9318void PersistentBase<T>::Reset() {
9319 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
9320 V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
9321 val_ = 0;
9322}

9330 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
9331 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);

9339 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9340 Reset();
9341 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
9342 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
9343}

9450template<typename T>
9451void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
9452 TYPE_CHECK(T, Number);
9453 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9454}
9455
9456template<typename T>
9457void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9458 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9459 typedef internal::Internals I;
9460 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9461 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9462 return;
9463 }
9464 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9465}
9466
9467template<typename T>
9468void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9469 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9470 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9471 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9472 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9473 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9474 return;
9475 }
9476 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9477}
9478
9479template<typename T>
9480void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9481 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9482 typedef internal::Internals I;
9483 int root_index;
9484 if (value) {
9485 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9486 } else {
9487 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9488 }
9489 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9490}
9491
9492template<typename T>
9493void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
9494 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9495 typedef internal::Internals I;
9496 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
9497}
9498
9499template<typename T>
9500void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
9501 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
9502 typedef internal::Internals I;
9503 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
9504}
9505
9506template<typename T>
9507void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
9508 TYPE_CHECK(T, String);
9509 typedef internal::Internals I;
9510 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
9511}
9512
9513template <typename T>
9514Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
9515 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
9516 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
9517}
9518
9519template <typename T>
9520Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
9521 typedef internal::Internals I;
9522 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
9523 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9524 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
9525}
9526
9527template <typename T>
9528template <typename S>
9529void ReturnValue<T>::Set(S* whatever) {
9530 // Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
9531 TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
9532}
9533
9534template<typename T>
9535internal::Object* ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
9536 // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
9537 return value_[-1];
9538}

9540template <typename T>

9546template<typename T>

9548 if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9549 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
9550}

9688
9689
9690Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9691#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9692 typedef internal::Object O;
9693 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9694 typedef internal::Internals I;
9695 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9696 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9697 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9698 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9699 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9700 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
9701 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9702 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9703 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9704 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9705 }
9706#endif
9707 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9708}
9709
9710
9711void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9712#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9713 typedef internal::Object O;
9714 typedef internal::Internals I;
9715 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9716 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9717 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9718 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9719 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9720 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
9721 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9722 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9723 }
9724#endif
9725 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9726}

9744
9745String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
9746 typedef internal::Object O;
9747 typedef internal::Internals I;
9748 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9749 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
9750 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
9751 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9752 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
9753 } else {
9754 result = NULL;
9755 }
9756#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9757 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
9758#endif
9759 return result;
9760}
9761
9762
9763String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
9764 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
9765 typedef internal::Object O;
9766 typedef internal::Internals I;
9767 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9768 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
9769 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
9770 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
9771 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
9772 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
9773 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9774 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
9775 }
9776#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9777 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
9778#endif
9779 return resource;
9780}

9791bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {

9795 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;

9797 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);

9826bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
9827 typedef internal::Object O;
9828 typedef internal::Internals I;
9829 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9830 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9831 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;

10288
10289
10290int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10291 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10292 typedef internal::Internals I;
10293 const int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10294 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10295 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10296 int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10297 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10298 int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10299 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10300 I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10301 const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
10302
10303 *external_memory = amount;
10304
10305 int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10306 *external_memory_at_last_mc - *external_memory;
10307 allocation_diff_since_last_mc = allocation_diff_since_last_mc < 0
10308 ? -allocation_diff_since_last_mc
10309 : allocation_diff_since_last_mc;
10310 if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10311 CheckMemoryPressure();
10312 }
10313
10314 if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10315 *external_memory_limit += change_in_bytes;
10316 }
10317
10318 if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10319 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10320 }
10321 return *external_memory;
10322}

10324Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10325#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10326 typedef internal::Object O;
10327 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
10328 typedef internal::Internals I;
10329 HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
10330 O** result =
10331 HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
10332 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10333#else
10334 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10335#endif
10336}
